        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Citadel Securities is making a major move into cryptocurrency market-making, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-01-03-2025-h2-2-signaling-increasing-institutional-confidence-in-digital-assets?source=website" target="_blank">signaling increasing institutional confidence in digital assets</a>. Once skeptical, the firm builds crypto liquidity teams overseas, focusing on major exchanges like Binance and Coinbase. Citadel’s plans could change based on how or if regulations roll out in the coming months.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">This shift aligns with evolving US regulations under President Trump, who aims to position the US as a global crypto leader. Citadel’s expertise could enhance market stability and risk management. Meanwhile, EDX Markets, backed by Citadel and Fidelity, is expanding in Singapore.</p>
